wbqev-crosscheck-explanation-general: General explanation text for special page.
wbqev-crosscheck-explanation-detail: Mre detailed explanation text for special page.
wbqev-crosscheck-form-entityid-placehold: Entity id placeholder for the input field.
wbqev-crosscheck-form-submit-label:
Label of the button, that starts the check.
{{Identical|Check}}
wbqev-crosscheck-invalid-entity-id: Error message that appears when the entered string is not a valid entity id.
wbqev-crosscheck-not-existent-entity: Error message that appears when the entered entity does not exist.
wbqev-crosscheck-result-headline: Headline that appears above the results. Has one parameter, that is the label of the entity, that was checked.
wbqev-crosscheck-empty-result: Message that appears, when the given entity has no statements that can be validated with any supported external database.
wbqev-crosscheck-result-table-header-loc: Header of the column that displays the data values stored in Wikidata.
wbqev-crosscheck-result-table-header-ext: Header of the column that displays the data values stored in external databases.
Header of the column that displays the name of the external source.
wbqev-crosscheck-result-table-header-sta:
Header of the column that shows the result of the constraint check.
{{Identical|Status}}
wbqev-crosscheck-status-match: Status for claims that have a match with any external data
wbqev-crosscheck-status-partial-match: Status for claims that have a potential match with any external data
wbqev-crosscheck-status-mismatch: Status for claims that have a mismatch with any external data.
wbqev-crosscheck-status-references-missi: Status for claims for which references are missing.
wbqev-crosscheck-status-references-state: Status for claims for which references are stated.
wbqev-externaldbs-overview-headline:
Headline that appears above the overview of external databases.
{{Identical|Database}}
wbqev-externaldbs-id:
Id of the dump of a external source.
{{Identical|ID}}
wbqev-externaldbs-import-date: Name for import date from the external source.
wbqev-externaldbs-language: Name for language from the external source.
wbqev-externaldbs-source-urls: Name for source url of the dump.
wbqev-externaldbs-size:
Name for size from the external source.
{{Identical|Size}}
wbqev-externaldbs-license:
Name for license from the external source.
{{Identical|License}}
wbqev-externaldbs-no-databases: Message that appears when no external databases exist.
wbq-subextension-name-wbqev: Name of this sub-extension. Shown in special page that lists all the violations.
wbqev-violation-header-external-source: Header for section in violations special page that displays the name of the external source.
wbqev-violation-header-local-value: Header for section in violations special page that displays the data values stored in external databases.
wbqev-violation-header-external-values: Header for section in violations special page that displays the name of the external source.
wbqev-violation-short-message: Short message that is shown for violated claims in pop-up on item page. First parameter is name of the data source.
wbqev-violation-long-message-headline: Header for long message that is shown for violated claims on item page.
wbqev-violation-long-message-external-va: Long message that is shown for violated claims on item page. First parameter are the external values, second parameter is the number of external values.
wbqev-violation-long-message-solve-issue: Message that is shown for violated claims in order to advise the user how to solve the issue.
